 Port Elizabeth -  According to data released by the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service, Port Alfred, 3rd Avenue Dip in Port Elizabeth, Port Elizabeth Airport, Riverstone Bridge and George, received much of the rain that fell over the Eastern and Southern Cape on Monday. Patensie, where the catchment areas of the Nelson Mandela Bay are located, received 21mm. Kareedouw and Kouga Dam - also sources of water for the Bay received 17mm and 10mm respectively. Station Names 28 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 27.0 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 35.8 ARS Blue Horizon Bay * AWSH Chatty * AWS Coega 8.0 AWSH Fettes Road 18.2 ARS Flower Reserve 16.0 Man Woodridge * AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 25.4 ARS St Albans 12.8 AWS Uitenhage *    Catchment  AWS Joubertina 5.0 Man Kareedouw 17.0 Man Kouga Dam 10.0 AWS Patensie 21.0 Man Swartkops  * Man   Other Towns  AWS Addo 19.6 AWS Bisho/KWT 5.0 AWS Cape St Francis 6.4 AWS Cradock 10.8 AWS East London 0.4 AWS Fort Beaufort 10.2 AWS George 24.3 AWS Graaff Reinet 19.0 AWS Grahamstown 10.0 AWS Henry`s Flats 15.2 AWS Joubertina 5.0 AWS Mossel Bay 5.4 AWS Mthatha NIL AWS Plettenberg bay 17.8 AWS Port Alfred 51.8 AWS Queenstown 0.8  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 